The National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) yesterday said company income tax (CIT) totaled N532.48 billion in first quarter 2022. According to its document titled “Company Income Tax Q1 2022,” the collection represented a 53.09 per cent growth rate on a quarter-on-quarter basis.   And God decided to show up, by Femi Adesina     Sen. Uba Sani wins Kaduna APC Gov ticket     Yilwada clinches Plateau APC Gov ticket   It added that local payments were N209.13 billion in the previous quarter, while foreign CIT raked in N323.13 billion. “On the aggregate, Company Income Tax (CIT) for first quarter 2022 was reported at N532.48 billion, a growth rate of 53.09 per cent on a quarter-on-quarter basis from N347.81billion in Q4 2021. Local payments recorded were N209.13 billion in Q1 2022, while foreign CIT payment contributed N323.35 billion. On a quarter-on-quarter basis, the activities of extraterritorial organizations and bodies recorded the highest growth rate with 60.61 per cent, followed by education with 39.76 per cent, and construction with 38.98 per cent.”